title: Independent Candidate wins PK-98 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Muhammad Sajjad has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-98, Karak -II by securing 37,160 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer his runner-up was an Independent candidate Malik Qasim Khan Khattak who bagged 31,853 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 46.69 per cent.
